  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Le 4:1, 2. Sin Offering of Ignorance.Of sins of ignorance, and their sacrifice,  Leviticus 4:1,2: committed by the priest according to the guilt of the people; he must offer a perfect young bullock, and sprinkle the blood seven times before the veil of the holy place, and upon the horns of the incense altar,  Leviticus 4:3-12. Or by the whole congregation, when their sin is known, the elders of the congregation to lay their hands on the head of the offering, to be offered in the same manner with that of the priest,  Leviticus 4:13-21. Or by a ruler, he, when his sin is made known to him, must offer a he-goat,  Leviticus 4:22-26. Or by a private person, must offer a female goat,  Leviticus 4:27-35: the sin is forgiven him.  No text from Poole on this verse. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Le 4:1, 2. Sin Offering of Ignorance.Of sins of ignorance, and their sacrifice, ",
            "children": []
          },
